---
exclude_paths:
  - roles/elliotweiser.osx-command-line-tools
  - files/observability
  # Track H Phase 6 (2026-05-01): pazny.dotfiles ships an upstream
  # Molecule test scaffold that references a `geerlingguy.git` role we
  # don't install (it's a Molecule-only test dep, not a runtime dep).
  # Excluding the molecule/ subdir keeps lint focused on runtime code.
  - roles/pazny.dotfiles/molecule

skip_list:
  - schema[meta]
  - role-name
  - experimental
  - fqcn
  - name[missing]
  - no-changed-when
  - risky-file-permissions
  - yaml
  # Track C/D (2026-04-26): the new pazny.linux.* roles use short var
  # prefixes (linux_docker_, hardening_) instead of the dotted role name
  # (pazny.linux.docker_) that ansible-lint expects. Same convention as
  # the pre-existing `uptime_kuma_*` defaults — the dotted form is
  # unwieldy in templates and tasks.
  - var-naming[no-role-prefix]
  - jinja[spacing]
  - name[template]

# Track H Phase 6 (2026-05-01): ansible-lint 26.x reports load-failure
# warnings on three include_tasks paths where the included file lives
# at the correct relative path (verified manually + --syntax-check OK
# on 2.20.5 + 2.21.0rc1) but lint resolves through a wrong stem
# (e.g. `tasks/stacks/tasks/stacks/...`). load-failure is unskippable
# per ansible-lint design; leaving these as WARNINGS (not errors) which
# don't fail CI. Upstream resolver fix will eventually clear them.
